This paper proposes a method to improve the performance of far-field speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as training a student model to imitate the output distributions of a teacher model, which falls under cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper uses parallel data to distill knowledge, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of KL divergence to minimize the difference between the output distributions of the teacher and student models is a statistical method, which is relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper aims to improve the performance of far-field speech recognition, which is a task in NLP and speech processing, and therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category.
